&quot;P.D. HAUGHTON BUYS BOSTON NATIONALS; Harvard Football Coach Heads Syndicate of Baseball Club Owners. &quot;
...
&quot;Percy D. Haughton, the famous Harvard football coach, today became President and part owner of the Boston National League Baseball Club. Associated with him as head of a syndicate of Boston men is Arthur C. Wise, member of a local banking firm. &quot;

The team he bought was the Boston Braves.
